{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17470941","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17470941"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"282"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17471285","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17471285"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T21:46:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T21:46:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"282"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"282","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/282"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.01,0.46,0.27,0.17]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"282"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92395"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"282","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/282"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"282"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75702"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"304"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"6222"},{"type":"tags","id":"12762"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"30348"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31572"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92395","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92395"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 2-year-old Indigenous child\u00a0from a remote community is being assessed because her parents are concerned because she has an abnormal gait . On examination, both hip joints are stiff and she leans to the left preferentially, with an obvious outward turn of the left leg and limp. She began walking at 18 months. On review of her birth notes, abnormal gluteal folds and leg length were noted.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA hip X-ray today shows findings consistent with a dislocated hip due to developmental dysplasia of the hip.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dennis-Browne brace","Curved sacral bar","Open reduction","Pavlik harness","Hip spica cast"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDevelopmental dysplasia of the hip (DDH) represents a wide spectrum of hip joint dysfunction including neonatal instability, acetabular dysplasia, hip subluxation and true dislocation of the hip. DDH alters hip biomechanics, predisposing to early osteoarthritis, and is the most common cause of total hip replacement in young people.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClinical screening, including instability manoeuvres should be performed universally as part of physical examination of the neonate. Limited hip abduction is the most important clinical sign. Splinting techniques such as the \u003Cstrong\u003EPavlik harness\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003EDennis-Browne brace\u003C/strong\u003E are used when the child is diagnosed in the first 6 months of life.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClosed reduction and application of a \u003Cstrong\u003Ehip spica cast\u003C/strong\u003E can be performed if these early interventions fail to maintain normal anatomical alignment. In children older than 6-8 months with a dislocated hip, a closed or \u003Cstrong\u003Eopen reduction\u003C/strong\u003E in theatre followed by spica cast immobilisation is indicated. Open reduction is preferred as the child becomes older. In this case of a late diagnosis of DDH with a dislocated hip, an open reduction is the most appropriate management option.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe normal age of presentation of DDH is between 6-12 months. It is possible the delay in this case was due to lack of screening facilities.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Open reduction is the most appropriate management option for a dislocated hip due to DDH in children older than 6-8 months\u0027 age"],"references":["Vaquero-Picado A, Gonz\u00e1lez-Mor\u00e1n G, Garay EG, Moraleda L. Developmental dysplasia of the hip: update of management. EFORT Open Rev. 2019;4(9):548-56."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75702"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"282"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75702","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75702"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-17T16:07:16+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-24T22:18:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"282"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92395"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","